---
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import '../../styles/main.css';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Three-D Models - Chapter 1 | Hacker1 v1.0</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Chapter 1: Dimensional Reality - Foundation principles of Three.js 3D modeling and scientific visualization." />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}favicon.svg`} />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Century+Schoolbook&family=Roboto:wght@400;500&family=EB+Garamond:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  </head>
  <body class="dark-mode three-d-background">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb">
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}`}>Home</a> → 
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}finished-work`}>Finished Work</a> → 
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}finished-work/three-d`}>Three-D</a> → 
        Chapter 1
      </nav>
      
      <h1>Three-D Models - Chapter 1: Dimensional Reality</h1>
      
      <div class="content-section implementation-background">
        <h2>The Architecture of Creation</h2>
        <p>
          "By faith we understand that the universe was formed at God's command, so that what is seen was not made out of what was visible." - Hebrews 11:3
        </p>
        <p>
          Three-dimensional modeling allows us to explore the spatial reality of God's creation, 
          from molecular structures to celestial mechanics. Through Three.js, we build digital 
          temples of understanding that reveal the architectural beauty of the physical universe.
        </p>
        
        <blockquote class="highlight">
          "The Lord by wisdom founded the earth; by understanding he established the heavens." - Proverbs 3:19
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <div class="content-section solution-background">
        <h2>Three.js as Digital Sculpting</h2>
        <p>
          Like God breathing life into clay, we use Three.js to breathe digital life into 
          geometric forms. Each 3D model is both scientific instrument and artistic expression, 
          revealing truths about structure, form, and dimensional relationships.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Core 3D Principles:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Geometric accuracy reflecting divine precision</li>
          <li>Lighting that reveals form and depth</li>
          <li>Interactive exploration enabling understanding</li>
          <li>Scientific accuracy in modeling natural phenomena</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Featured 3D Categories:</h3>
        <div class="model-showcase">
          <div class="model-item">
            <div class="model-demo">
              <div class="placeholder-3d">
                <div class="cube">
                  <div class="face front"></div>
                  <div class="face back"></div>
                  <div class="face right"></div>
                  <div class="face left"></div>
                  <div class="face top"></div>
                  <div class="face bottom"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <h4>Geometric Solids</h4>
            <p>Platonic solids and sacred geometry in three-dimensional space.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="model-item">
            <div class="model-demo">
              <div class="placeholder-3d">
                <div class="sphere-system">
                  <div class="sphere large"></div>
                  <div class="sphere medium"></div>
                  <div class="sphere small"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <h4>Molecular Models</h4>
            <p>Atomic and molecular structures revealing the building blocks of creation.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="model-item">
            <div class="model-demo">
              <div class="placeholder-3d">
                <div class="spiral-model">
                  <div class="spiral-path"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <h4>Astronomical Models</h4>
            <p>Planetary motion and celestial mechanics displaying cosmic order.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-section experimental-background">
        <h2>Interactive 3D Experiences</h2>
        <p>
          "When I consider your heavens, the work of your fingers, the moon and the stars, 
          which you have set in place..." - Psalm 8:3. Interactive 3D models allow us to 
          examine creation from impossible perspectives, rotating, zooming, and exploring 
          the intricate details of God's handiwork.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Interaction Features:</h3>
        <div class="interaction-features">
          <div class="feature-item">
            <h4>Orbital Controls</h4>
            <p>Mouse and touch controls for examining models from every angle, like walking around a sculpture in a gallery.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-item">
            <h4>Dynamic Lighting</h4>
            <p>Adjustable lighting to reveal surface details and create dramatic shadows that enhance understanding.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-item">
            <h4>Animation Systems</h4>
            <p>Time-based animations showing processes like molecular bonding or planetary orbits.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-item">
            <h4>Cross-Sections</h4>
            <p>Cut-away views revealing internal structures, from crystal lattices to anatomical details.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="navigation-section">
        <div class="nav-buttons">
          <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}finished-work/two-d-ch1`} class="button is-light">← Previous: Two-D Chapter 1</a>
          <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}finished-work/action-ch1`} class="button is-primary">Next: Action Chapter 1 →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Add the custom floating bottom navbar -->
    <Navbar />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: white;
  }

  h1 {
    color: #e8d5b7;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #8b7355;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .content-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    color: #f0f0f0;
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    color: #e8d5b7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #8b7355;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .content-section h3 {
    color: #d4af37;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .content-section h4 {
    color: #e8d5b7;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .highlight {
    background: rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.1);
    border-left: 4px solid #d4af37;
    padding: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .model-showcase {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .model-item {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 3px solid #8b7355;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .model-demo {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    height: 120px;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .placeholder-3d {
    perspective: 600px;
  }

  .cube {
    width: 60px;
    height: 60px;
    position: relative;
    transform-style: preserve-3d;
    animation: rotate 4s infinite linear;
  }

  .face {
    position: absolute;
    width: 60px;
    height: 60px;
    border: 2px solid #D4AF37;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .front { transform: rotateY(0deg) translateZ(30px); background: rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.1); }
  .back { transform: rotateY(180deg) translateZ(30px); background: rgba(138, 90, 90, 0.1); }
  .right { transform: rotateY(90deg) translateZ(30px); background: rgba(90, 122, 90, 0.1); }
  .left { transform: rotateY(-90deg) translateZ(30px); background: rgba(122, 90, 122, 0.1); }
  .top { transform: rotateX(90deg) translateZ(30px); background: rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.2); }
  .bottom { transform: rotateX(-90deg) translateZ(30px); background: rgba(138, 90, 90, 0.2); }

  .sphere-system {
    position: relative;
    width: 80px;
    height: 80px;
  }

  .sphere {
    position: absolute;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 2px solid #8A5A5A;
    animation: orbit 3s infinite linear;
  }

  .sphere.large {
    width: 30px;
    height: 30px;
    background: rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.3);
    top: 25px;
    left: 25px;
  }

  .sphere.medium {
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    background: rgba(138, 90, 90, 0.3);
    top: 5px;
    left: 30px;
    animation-duration: 2s;
  }

  .sphere.small {
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    background: rgba(90, 122, 90, 0.3);
    top: 35px;
    left: 5px;
    animation-duration: 1.5s;
  }

  .spiral-model {
    width: 80px;
    height: 80px;
    border: 2px dashed #7A5A7A;
    border-radius: 50%;
    position: relative;
    animation: rotate 5s infinite linear;
  }

  .spiral-path {
    position: absolute;
    width: 60px;
    height: 60px;
    top: 8px;
    left: 8px;
    border: 2px solid #D4AF37;
    border-radius: 50%;
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .interaction-features {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .feature-item {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 3px solid #8b7355;
  }

  .navigation-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  }

  .nav-buttons {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .button {
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .button.is-light {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    color: #f0f0f0;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .button.is-light:hover {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .button.is-primary {
    background: #8b7355;
    color: white;
    border: 1px solid #8b7355;
  }

  .button.is-primary:hover {
    background: #a0845f;
  }

  @keyframes rotate {
    0% { transform: rotateX(0deg) rotateY(0deg); }
    100% { transform: rotateX(360deg) rotateY(360deg); }
  }

  @keyframes orbit {
    0% { transform: rotate(0deg) translateX(20px) rotate(0deg); }
    100% { transform: rotate(360deg) translateX(20px) rotate(-360deg); }
  }

  /* Add padding to body to prevent navbar overlap */
  body {
    padding-bottom: 100px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .nav-buttons {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
    
    .container {
      padding: 1rem;
    }

    .model-showcase, .interaction-features {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
